I will never bob for apples, though, because of this. I had no urge to bob for apples before, but now I have a specific need to never do it, and a hope that I have never tried it as a young child and forgotten, or something.

If you want something from childhoods ... try "koek happen" (Dutch don't know the correct translation; cake biting)

Make sure that there is a line with enough length that multiple people can "bite" at the same time each on their own "cake".

The cake must hang at their eye height so that they can reach it but only with some effort (standing on your toes)

and the goal is ...
A. eat it while on the line
B. get it off the line, but make sure it does not fall on the ground ... you don't eat stuff that has fallen on the floor Arin.

I am sure that some other dutchies can help me get the correct translation.

Oude wijve (koek), ontbijtkoek.
